Rating: 4
I made this recipe for a dinner group with a Mediterranean theme all of us liked it however I doubled the filling and let it sit overnight chilled and added it to the tart shell about 3 hours before I was ready to serve it and it worked out great--I'll make it again doing the same thing. I used an 11 inch tart pan with a removeable bottom.

Rating: 4
I love lemon tart and I have made many but this one is the best. I used the optional zest because I like a lemon dessert to be tart. The crust is very fragile and hard to work with so I just pressed it in the pan. When it's baked you can't tell the difference. I served with Lemoncello as suggested by the article and all of my guests cleaned their plates!

